---

## Why this license?

KL Sync scrapes KL University's ERP without official permission. This creates legal gray area — the university could shut it down at any time. A permissive license (MIT, Apache, etc.) would let anyone fork, rebrand, and host it elsewhere, which could escalate the legal risk to the original author.

This restrictive license keeps the project under control and lets me be transparent about the risks.

If the university formally endorses this project or provides API access, we'll relicense it under something more open.
